If the table is a parent table, then this array is populated with the names of all child tables of the given table. If tableName is an empty string, then the array contains the names of all top-level tables in GPUdb.

      • getSizes

        public List<Long> getSizes()
        Returns:
        Empty array if the 'get_sizes' option is 'false'. Otherwise, sizes of the respective tables represented in tableNames. For all but track data types, this is simply the number of total objects in a table. For track types, since each track semantically contains many individual objects, the 'size' is the count of 'conceptual' tracks (each of which may be associated with multiple objects).

      • getFullSizes

        public List<Long> getFullSizes()
        Returns:
        Empty array if the 'get_sizes' option is 'false'. Otherwise, number of total objects in the respective tables represented in tableNames. For all but track data types, this is the same as sizes. For track types, since each track semantically contains many individual objects, the 'full size' is the count of total objects.
